news.title: DDA invites bids for five-star hotel in Dwarka’s Sector 23
news.para: The Delhi Development Authority (DDA) is seeking a licensee for a five-star hotel in Dwarka's Sector 23, following the successful leasing of a site in Nehru Place. This 2.5-acre land parcel will be leased for 55 years, with the selected agency responsible for developing and managing a 200-room hotel.

news.title: DTCP demolishes illegal gates, guard room in Gurugram sector 85
news.para: Gurugram's Department of Town and Country Planning (DTCP) demolished illegal gates and a guard room erected by Orris Infrastructure in Sector 85, addressing resident complaints about restricted access on public roads. The DTCP also removed an encroachment by an RWA in Uppal Southend, Sector 49, where a road was illegally converted into a park.

news.title: YEIDA board gives nod for developed plots for farmers, urban centres in Hathras, Agra
news.para: YEIDA has approved several key proposals, including allotting developed plots to farmers and developing 29 smart villages with modern amenities. The authority will establish urban centers in Hathras and Agra to boost industrial and residential growth.

news.title: Bhubaneswar civic body partners with a bank for home loans to urban poor
news.para: To ease home loan access for affordable housing beneficiaries, the Bhubaneswar Municipal Corporation (BMC) has collaborated with a private bank. This partnership aims to assist urban poor beneficiaries in understanding banking norms and contributing their share for allotted houses under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (Urban) 2.0. A pilot project will involve 600 beneficiaries facing difficulties.

news.title: RISE Infraventures targets ₹160 crore revenue in FY26
news.para: RISE Infraventures aims for ₹160 crore revenue by FY26, doubling from ₹80 crore in FY25 with a 25% profit margin. Investing ₹10 crore in commercial real estate leasing, the firm targets one million sq ft of transactions worth over ₹1,000 crore in 12-18 months. With new leadership and expansion, they anticipate adding 25-30% new clients.

news.title: Max Estates secures development rights of 7.25 acre land in Gurugram
news.para: Max Estates has acquired development rights for a 7.25-acre land parcel in Gurugram's Sector 59 through the purchase of Base Buildwell. This project, with an expected outlay of ₹534 crore, boasts a development potential of 1.3 million sq ft and is projected to generate a booking value exceeding ₹3,000 crore.

news.title: Residents pay the price for Rajasthan housing board delay
news.para: Indira Gandhi Nagar residents are facing hazardous road conditions due to an unfinished 100-metre stretch near Kundanpura. Despite a High Court order six months ago to complete the road, the Rajasthan Housing Board (RHB) has yet to resume construction, allegedly due to encroachment issues and a nexus between officials and contractors.

news.title: NGT imposes ₹2.5 crore cost on developer for Thergaon project built without environment clearance
news.para: The National Green Tribunal has directed a developer to pay Rs2.55 crore as environmental compensation for constructing a residential project in Thergaon without mandatory environmental clearance. The project, consisting of 497 flats and 25 commercial units, violated the Environment Impact Assessment notification.

news.title: Goa: GIDC seeks to double FAR for four lakh sq meter Verna IT park
news.para: The Goa Industrial Development Corporation (GIDC) is planning to double the permissible floor area ratio (FAR) for its proposed 'Hello World' IT Park in Verna, pending government approval. This move aims to attract developers and boost the project's financial viability.

news.title: Cannot deny building nod based on 100-year-old street plans: Calcutta HC
news.para: The Calcutta High Court has ruled against the Kolkata Municipal Corporation (KMC), stating that building permission cannot be denied based on a nearly century-old street plan. The court cancelled the alignments of two streets, planned in 1930 but never implemented, which KMC had used to deny building plan permissions.

news.title: CEC advises against sweeping demolition drives in Aravalis
news.para: The central empowered committee (CEC) has suggested differentiating between houses in village areas and illegal constructions in Faridabad's Aravalis, in a report submitted to the Supreme Court. The report recommends dealing with large projects and farmhouses on forest land as per norms. The Supreme Court is scheduled to examine the report on September 8.

news.title: Safety violations in highrise constructions in Maharashtra will result in civil & criminal actions
news.para: In response to rising safety concerns and fatal accidents involving high-rise construction, the Mumbai Metropolitan Region mandates strict adherence to safety protocols for working at heights. Planning authorities must incorporate safety recommendations into development permissions, with violations leading to civil and criminal actions.

news.title: Karnataka housing board clears integrated township on 43 acres in Yelahanka
news.para: Karnataka Housing Board's Chikkajala township project in Yelahanka, estimated at Rs 2,930 crore, has received cabinet approval under a PPP model on a 43-acre plot. Despite ongoing land disputes, development will proceed after securing necessary approvals from BIAAPA. The project, expected to generate Rs 1,252 crore in revenue for the board, involves no additional KHB investment beyond land sharing.

news.title: New circle rates of Kanpur implemented
news.para: Kanpur Nagar has implemented amended land circle rates starting Friday, September 5th, introducing significant changes to general guidelines. These revisions include depreciation on multi-story residential buildings, abolition of common facility fees, and depreciation on large non-agricultural plots.

news.title: Builder paid Vasai ex-civic chief, town planner ₹15 crore bribe: ED
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) alleges that builder paid Anil Pawar, former Vasai-Virar civic chief, and Y S Reddy, deputy director of town planning, ₹15 crore in bribes for project clearances. Both were arrested in connection with an illegal construction and corruption racket. Reddy is remanded in ED custody for further investigation into property documents and high-value transactions.

news.title: Realtors take cue from Purple, Blue Line extension, bullish on new links
news.para: Kolkata's metro expansion is set to revolutionize the real estate sector, boosting office and residential development, particularly in areas like Salt Lake, New Town, and northern suburbs. Reduced travel times are making previously less accessible locations attractive to homebuyers and developers, unlocking new land and driving demand for mid-range and luxury properties.

news.title: House prices in UK rise 0.3% in August: Halifax
news.para: British house prices experienced a 0.3% increase in August, marking the third consecutive monthly rise and pushing them 2.2% higher than the previous year, according to Halifax. Despite some uncertainty in the wider economy, the housing market demonstrates resilience, supported by improving affordability and steady demand. The average property price reached a new record high of 299,331 pounds.

news.title: Philippines extends land leases to 99 years to attract foreign investors
news.para: President Marcos Jr. has signed a law allowing foreign investors to lease private land in the Philippines for up to 99 years, replacing the previous 50-year limit with a 25-year extension. This aims to attract more offshore funding for long-term commercial and industrial projects, addressing investor concerns about lease contract stability.

news.title: Delhi: All 152 DDA flats sold within an hour under 'Apna Ghar Aawas Yojana'
news.para: Delhi Development Authority's 'Apna Ghar Aawas Yojana' witnessed remarkable success as all 152 flats were booked within an hour, projecting a revenue of Rs 100 crores. Due to high public demand, DDA has extended the scheme until November 26, 2025, offering ready-to-move-in flats across various categories and locations.

news.title: Vedanta beats Adani Group with ₹17,000 crore bid to acquire Jaiprakash Associates
news.para: Vedanta Group has emerged as the winning bidder for the debt-ridden Jaiprakash Associates (JAL), surpassing Adani Group with a Rs 17,000 crore offer. This bid translates to a net present value of Rs 12,505 crore for JAL, which faced insolvency proceedings due to loan defaults. The acquisition marks a significant development in the resolution of JAL's financial distress.
